Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the undecidability of certain logics that are relevant to artificial intelligence, such as modal logics, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with formal languages and grammars, which are studied in cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper's focus on undecidability results suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
